Name: Lowest Temperature Limit
Help: Cut out temperature at coldest position of the spindle (thermostat kNob)
ChineseHelp: Cut out temperature at coldest position of the spindle (thermostat kNob)

Name: Highest Temperature Limit
Help: Cut out temperature at warmest position of the spindle (thermostat kNob)
ChineseHelp: Cut out temperature at warmest position of the spindle (thermostat kNob)

Name: Lowest Temperature Differential
Help: This defines the difference between the cut-out and the cut-in at coldest position of thermostat
ChineseHelp: This defines the difference between the cut-out and the cut-in at coldest position of thermostat

Name: Highest Temperature Differential
Help: This defines the difference between the cut-out and the cut-in at warmest position of thermostat
ChineseHelp: This defines the difference between the cut-out and the cut-in at warmest position of thermostat

Name: Fan Control Method
Help:
Defines the Fan control method
FAo- Fan always on
FFC- Fan follow compressor (Fan runs only when compressor is On)
FPL- Fan Cycling (Fan cycling during compressor off cycle)
ChineseHelp:
Defines the Fan control method
FAo- Fan always on
FFC- Fan follow compressor (Fan runs only when compressor is On)
FPL- Fan Cycling (Fan cycling during compressor off cycle)

Name: Fan ON Delay
Help: Time delay to start the fan after compressor cut-in
ChineseHelp: Time delay to start the fan after compressor cut-in

Name: Fan Stop Delay
Help: Time delay to stop the fan after compressor cut-out
ChineseHelp: Time delay to stop the fan after compressor cut-out

Name: Fan On Cycle
Help: If fan control method is selected as "FPL" this parameter defines the fan ON time during fan pulsating cycle
ChineseHelp: If fan control method is selected as "FPL" this parameter defines the fan ON time during fan pulsating cycle

Name: Fan Stop Cycle
Help: If fan control method is selected as "FPL" this parameter defines the fan OFF time during fan pulsating cycle
ChineseHelp: If fan control method is selected as "FPL" this parameter defines the fan OFF time during fan pulsating cycle

Name: Fan stop delay on door open
Help: The delay to stop the fan after the door has been opened"0"- fan stop immediately when door open"1-998"- delay for fan stop after door open"999"- fan keep running all the time during door open
ChineseHelp: The delay to stop the fan after the door has been opened"0"- fan stop immediately when door open"1-998"- delay for fan stop after door open"999"- fan keep running all the time during door open
VariableName: Fan Stop Time on Door Open

Name: Fan Minimum Stop Time
Help: Minimum time fan must stop whenever it is switched off
ChineseHelp: Minimum time fan must stop whenever it is switched off

Name: Fan Limit Temperature
Help: This function prevents the evaporator fan to operate if the temperature is above the fan limit temperature. If the defrost sensor registers a higher temperature than the one set here, the fan will be stopped to avoid the warm air circulation in the cabinet. Fan will restart when evap temperature goes 2 degC less than FLt (FLt-2 DegC). This parameter is active only when evaporator sensor is configured
ChineseHelp: This function prevents the evaporator fan to operate if the temperature is above the fan limit temperature. If the defrost sensor registers a higher temperature than the one set here, the fan will be stopped to avoid the warm air circulation in the cabinet. Fan will restart when evap temperature goes 2 degC less than FLt (FLt-2 DegC). This parameter is active only when evaporator sensor is configured

Name: Min Run time
Help: To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-outs, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor runs for atleast the specified time. This parameter overrides the cut-out temperature. [Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary deep temperatures]
ChineseHelp: To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-outs, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor runs for atleast the specified time. This parameter overrides the cut-out temperature. [Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary deep temperatures]

Name: Min Stop time
Help: To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-ins, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor remains off for atleast the specified time under this parameter. This parameter overrides the cut-in temperatures. [Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary warm temperatures]
ChineseHelp: To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-ins, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor remains off for atleast the specified time under this parameter. This parameter overrides the cut-in temperatures. [Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary warm temperatures]

Name: Compressor Door open delay
Help: This parameter sets the delay in stopping the compressor when  door is opened. If set "0" compressor stops immediately. If set 15 it will disable the functionality and does not stop the compressor
ChineseHelp: This parameter sets the delay in stopping the compressor when  door is opened. If set "0" compressor stops immediately. If set 15 it will disable the functionality and does not stop the compressor

Name: System Resume after door open
Help: If door is kept open for long time, compressor and fan will resume after this time if they switched off due to door open. [Note : 'Srt' must be always greater than' Cdd' and 'Fdt']If Srt=0, System resume feature disabled and system will resume only when the door is closed.
ChineseHelp: If door is kept open for long time, compressor and fan will resume after this time if they switched off due to door open. [Note : 'Srt' must be always greater than' Cdd' and 'Fdt']If Srt=0, System resume feature disabled and system will resume only when the door is closed.

Name: Power On Delay
Help: This is the delay in seconds between power-on and the output relays being activated
ChineseHelp: This is the delay in seconds between power-on and the output relays being activated

Name: Low temp Alarm limit
Help: If cabinet air temperature goes below this value will raise low temperature alarm  (All these alarm status can be viewed only in KoolProg)
ChineseHelp: If cabinet air temperature goes below this value will raise low temperature alarm  (All these alarm status can be viewed only in KoolProg)

Name: High temp Alarm limit
Help: If cabinet air temperature goes above this value will raise low temperature alarm
ChineseHelp: If cabinet air temperature goes above this value will raise low temperature alarm

Name: Low temp Alarm delay
Help: Time delay to raise alarm once low temperature alarm limit is reached
ChineseHelp: Time delay to raise alarm once low temperature alarm limit is reached

Name: High temp Alarm delay
Help: Time delay to raise alarm once high temperature alarm limit is reached
ChineseHelp: Time delay to raise alarm once high temperature alarm limit is reached

Name: Alarm Door open delay
Help: Time delay to raise alarm if the door is kept open. If the door is closed before the delay time, it will not raise alarm
ChineseHelp: Time delay to raise alarm if the door is kept open. If the door is closed before the delay time, it will not raise alarm

Name: ECO Mode Enable
Help: ECO mode is active or not. If selected "No" all other settings related to ECO mode are not active
ChineseHelp: ECO mode is active or not. If selected "No" all other settings related to ECO mode are not active

Name: Voltage Protection function
Help: This feature protects the compressor if the line voltage goes beyond the operating range
ChineseHelp: This feature protects the compressor if the line voltage goes beyond the operating range

Name: Operating mode
Help: Normal mode - Normal operation mode of the controllerManual mode- In this mode output relays can be switched ON and OFF irrespective of temperature conditions
ChineseHelp: Normal mode - Normal operation mode of the controllerManual mode- In this mode output relays can be switched ON and OFF irrespective of temperature conditions

Name: Test mode setpoint
Help: Test mode setpoint
ChineseHelp: Test mode setpoint

Name: Alarm delay during Pull Down/ Power up /defrost
ChineseName: 下拉/加电/除霜期间的报警延迟
Help: Time delay to raise high temperature alarm during pull down, power up and defrost in order to avoid wrong alarm signal during these conditions
ChineseHelp: Time delay to raise high temperature alarm during pull down, power up and defrost in order to avoid wrong alarm signal during these condtions
VariableName: Alarm delay during Pull Down/ Power up /defrost

Name: Initial pull down ON/OFF
Help:
Initial Pull down 
oFF- Disable
on- Enable
Initial pull down (IPD) is to provide faster cooling when the cabinet is powered up with warmer inside temperature.  During IPD, defrost will be skipped until cabinet air temperature reaches cut out temperature or IPD duration expires. IPD operates only during power up and can be enabled/disabled using this parameter
ChineseHelp:
Initial Pull down 
oFF- Disable
on- Enable
Initial pull down (IPD) is to provide faster cooling when the cabinet is powered up with warmer inside temperature.  During IPD, defrost will be skipped until cabinet air temperature reaches cut out temperature or IPD duration expires. IPD operates only during power up and can be enabled/disabled using this parameter

Name: Relay 1 Switch
Help: Turn On Relay 1 Switch Manually
ChineseHelp: Turn On Relay 1 Switch Manually

Name: Relay 2 Switch
Help: Turn On Relay 2 Switch Manually
ChineseHelp: Turn On Relay 2 Switch Manually

Name: Minimum Cut-in Voltage
Help: The lowest voltage at which the compressor is allowed to Cut-in
ChineseHelp: The lowest voltage at which the compressor is allowed to Cut-in

Name: Minimum Cut out Voltage
Help: When the compressor is running, if voltage goes below this value, it will switch off the compressor.  This parameter is to avoid sudden switching on and off of compressor due to voltage fluctuations. This cut-off voltage will override compressor minimum run time
ChineseHelp: When the compressor is running, if voltage goes below this value, it will switch off the compressor.  This parameter is to avoid sudden switching on and off of compressor due to voltage fluctuations. This cut-off voltage will override compressor minimum run time

Name: Maximum cut out Voltage
Help:
when the compressor is running, it will be switched off if the voltage exceeds this value
If the compressor is already stopped, it will remain switched off
ChineseHelp:
when the compressor is running, it will be switched off if the voltage exceeds this value
If the compressor is already stopped, it will remain switched off

Name: IPD and Pull down Duration
Help: Maximum time IPD and Pull down can run. IPD and Pull down will terminate as soon as this time expires regardless of cab air temperature
ChineseHelp: Maximum time IPD and Pull down can run. IPD and Pull down will terminate as soon as this time expires regardless of cab air temperature

Name: Pull down and IPD Initiate Temp
Help: This parameter indicates the temperature at which IPD or Pulldown will be initiated. - At Power up: If cab air temp>Pit for more than 5 minutes trigger the Initial pull down.- During normal operation:  if the cab air temp stays above Pit>1hr trigger the Pull down
ChineseHelp: This parameter indicates the temperature at which IPD or Pulldown will be initiated. - At Power up: If cab air temp>Pit for more than 5 minutes trigger the Initial pull down.- During normal operation:  if the cab air temp stays above Pit>1hr trigger the Pull down
VariableName: Pull down and IPD Initiate Temp

Name: Pull Down Limit Temp
Help: This parameter sets the cut out temperature during Pull-down cycle to achieve more cooling. Controller will exit the pull down once this temperature is achieved or expiry of  pull down duration (IPD)
ChineseHelp: This parameter sets the cut out temperature during Pull-down cycle to achieve more cooling. Controller will exit the pull down once this temperature is achieved or expiry of  pull down duration (IPD)

Name: Eco Offset
Help: Defines offset temperature during ECO mode. Offset can be positive or negative
ChineseHelp: Defines offset temperature during ECO mode. Offset can be positive or negative

Name: Eco Door Delay
Help: Time delay for entering in to ECO mode if there is no door open
ChineseHelp: Time delay for entering in to ECO mode if there is no door open

Name: Condenser Alarm Limit
Help: This parameter sets the condenser temperature at which an alarm will be generated
ChineseHelp: This parameter sets the condenser temperature at which an alarm will be generated

Name: Condenser Block Limit
Help: This parameter sets the compressor switched off due to high condenser temperature
ChineseHelp: This parameter sets the compressor switched off due to high condenser temperature

Name: Condenser OK Limit
Help: This parameter sets the compressor to switch On again after switched off due to  high condenser temperature respecting minimum compressor stop time
ChineseHelp: This parameter sets the compressor to switch On again after switched off due to  high condenser temperature respecting minimum compressor stop time

Name: Control sensor error handling type
Help:
Method to control the cooling cycle in case of cabinet air sensor error
"No": No sensor error handling
"SEt": Follow configured error run and stop time
"Aut" : Control automaticaly based on past cycles time
ChineseHelp:
Method to control the cooling cycle in case of cabinet air sensor error
"No": No sensor error handling
"SEt": Follow configured error run and stop time
"Aut" : Control automaticaly based on past cycles time

Name: Error Run Time
Help: Cooling cycle ON time in case of cabinet sensor error (Active only if EHd=SEt)
ChineseHelp: Cooling cycle ON time in case of cabinet sensor error (Active only if EHd=SEt)

Name: Error Stop Time
Help: Cooling cycle off time in case of cabinet sensor error (Active only if EHd=SEt)
ChineseHelp: Cooling cycle off time in case of cabinet sensor error (Active only if EHd=SEt)

Name: Zero Cross Config
Help: This parameter enhances the relay life and also avoid relay sparks during relay on and off. If selected "Yes"relays will be switched on and off when the line-voltage is closeer to zero
ChineseHelp: This parameter enhances the relay life and also avoid relay sparks during relay on and off. If selected "Yes"relays will be switched on and off when the line-voltage is closeer to zero

Name: Defrost Status (Stages)
Help:
1- Idle
2- Ice off
3- Drip off
4- Cooling preparation after defrost
ChineseHelp:
1- Idle
2- Ice off
3- Drip off
4- Cooling preparation after defrost

Name: Defrost type
Help: This parameter defines the required type of defrostno- Defrost function is disablednAt- Natural defrost (OFF-cycle defrost)EL- Electrical defrostHgd- Hot gas defrost
ChineseHelp:
This parameter defines the required type of defrost
No- Defrost function is disabled
nAt- Natural defrost (OFF-cycle defrost)
EL- Electrical defrost
Hgd- Hot gas defrost

Name: Minimum defrost Interval
Help: Defines the minimum time period between the start of two defrost cycles. If the evaporator temperature goes below the defrost start temperature (dEt) controller triggers the defrost after this period, if not trigger the defrost at Maximum defrost interval (dAi)
ChineseHelp: Defines the minimum time period between the start of two defrost cycles. If the evaporator temperature goes below the defrost start temperature (dEt) controller triggers the defrost after this period, if not trigger the defrost at Maximum defrost interval (dAi)

Name: Maximum defrost Interval
Help: Maximum time period between the start of two defrost cycles
ChineseHelp: Maximum time period between the start of two defrost cycles

Name: Maximum defrost Time
Help: Maximum duration of a defrost cycle. Controller will terminate the defrost after this time, even if evap sensor is configured and evaporator temperature is less than terminate temperature (dtt)
ChineseHelp: Maximum duration of a defrost cycle. Controller will terminate the defrost after this time, even if evap sensor is configured and evaporator temperature is less than terminate temperature (dtt)

Name: Defrost Terminate Temp
Help: This parameter defines the evaporator temperature at which defrost must be terminated. controller will terminate the defrost based on the defrost terminate temperature (dtt) or Maximum defrost time (dAt). If no evaporator sensor is used, defrost would be terminated based on the maximum defrost time (dAt)
ChineseHelp: This parameter defines the evaporator temperature at which defrost must be terminated. controller will terminate the defrost based on the defrost terminate temperature (dtt) or Maximum defrost time (dAt). If no evaporator sensor is used, defrost would be terminated based on the maximum defrost time (dAt)

Name: Defrost on accumulated Compressor Run Time
ChineseName: 基于压缩机运行时间化霜
Help: If this parameter is set to "Yes", defrost interval is calculated based on the total time the compressor has been running. If this parameter is set to No, then defrost interval is based on the elapsed time,regardless of compressor ON time
ChineseHelp: If this parameter is set to "Yes", defrost interval is calculated based on the total time the compressor has been running. If this parameter is set to No, then defrost interval is based on the elapsed time,regardless of compressor ON time
VariableName: Defrost On accumulated Compressor Run Time

Name: Defrost Start by Evap Temp
Help: Evaporator Temperature at which the defrost to be triggered after minimum defrost interval to avoid excess frost on the evaporator (Active only if evaporator sensor is configured)
ChineseHelp: Evaporator Temperature at which the defrost to be triggered after minimum defrost interval to avoid excess frost on the evaporator (Active only if evaporator sensor is configured)

Name: Drip Off time
Help: Defines the time delay to start compressor after terminating defrost. This feature is to ensure no water droplet on the evaporator before starting the cooling cycle
ChineseHelp: Defines the time delay to start compressor after terminating defrost. This feature is to ensure no water droplet on the evaporator before starting the cooling cycle

Name: Fan Delay After Defrost
ChineseName: 除霜后风扇延迟除霜后风扇延迟
Help: Defines delay in switching ON the fan  from compressor start after defrost to avoid warm air circulation
ChineseHelp: Defines delay in switching ON the fan  from compressor start after defrost to avoid warm air circulation

Name: Fan Start Temperature after defrost
Help: This parameter determines at what evaporator temperature the fan will start after a defrost cycle. If the time set in "Fdd" occurs before the temperature set in "Ftd", the fan will start in line with "Fdd". If the temperature set in "Ftd" occurs first, then the fan will start in line with "Ftd"
ChineseHelp: This parameter determines at what evaporator temperature the fan will start after a defrost cycle. If the time set in "Fdd" occurs before the temperature set in "Ftd", the fan will start in line with "Fdd". If the temperature set in "Ftd" occurs first, then the fan will start in line with "Ftd"

Name: Fan ON during Defrost
Help: Defines the status of fan during defrost. Set to "Yes", the fan will run during defrost cycles and set to "No", will keep the fan off during defrost cycles
ChineseHelp: Defines the status of fan during defrost. Set to "Yes", the fan will run during defrost cycles and set to "No", will keep the fan off during defrost cycles

Name: Initial Defrost Interval
Help: The initial defrost interval determines the time for first defrost after power-up. The initial defrost is mainly intended for factory testing of the defrost functionality and can be set to expire after a number compressor cycles according to the setting of parameter "idd"
ChineseHelp: The initial defrost interval determines the time for first defrost after power-up. The initial defrost is mainly intended for factory testing of the defrost functionality and can be set to expire after a number compressor cycles according to the setting of parameter "idd"

Name: Initial Defrost duration
Help:
The initial defrost duration is the number of compressor cycles after which initial defrost is deactivated.
"0"-  No initial defrost
"1-998"- number of compressor cycles before deactivation
"999"- initial defrost always active
ChineseHelp:
The initial defrost duration is the number of compressor cycles after which initial defrost is deactivated.
"0"-  No initial defrost

"999"- initial defrost always active

ChineseName: 泄漏报警压缩机运行时间

If compressor operates continuously for more than the time configured in this parameter Leakage alarm will be triggered. Generally this value to be set higher than pull down duration "Pdd". 
"0": disable

Name: Minimum defrost time
Help: Defines the minimum duration of a defrost cycle. During this period, the controller will not check the temperature. Once the minimum time has expired, the temperature will be checked and if the terminate temperature "dtt" has been reached, the defrost cycle will end. If dtt has not been reached, defrost will continue until maximum defrost time "dAt" reached.
ChineseHelp: Defines the minimum duration of a defrost cycle. During this period, the controller will not check the temperature. Once the minimum time has expired, the temperature will be checked and if the terminate temperature "dtt" has been reached, the defrost cycle will end. If dtt has not been reached, defrost will continue until maximum defrost time "dAt" reached.

Name: Holiday Mode
Help: Holiday mode is active or not. If selected "No"  all other settings related to holiday mode are not active
ChineseHelp: Holiday mode is active or not. If selected "No"  all other settings related to holiday mode are not active

Name: Holiday Length
Help: Criteria for entering holiday mode based on number of hours of no activity in ECO mode. If controller does not detect any activity after enetering ECO mode for these many hours it will trigger the Holiday mode and set the temperature as per holiday offset
ChineseHelp: Criteria for entering holiday mode based on number of hours of no activity in ECO mode. If controller does not detect any activity after enetering ECO mode for these many hours it will trigger the Holiday mode and set the temperature as per holiday offset

Name: Holiday Temperature offset
Help: Defines the offset temperature during holiday mode. Offset can be possitive or negative.
ChineseHelp: Defines the offset temperature during holiday mode. Offset can be possitive or negative.

Name: Automatic Heater Control Mode
Help: Automatic heater control /dual mode is to protect food items stored in cabinet from frozen during the winter when installed outdoor. Automatic heater control uses the defrost heater to increase the cabinet temperature when it goes below the cut out temperature during Cooling mode.No: This feature is disabledYes: Feature is active
ChineseHelp: Automatic heater control /dual mode is to protect food items stored in cabinet from frozen during the winter when installed outdoor. Automatic heater control uses the defrost heater to increase the cabinet temperature when it goes below the cut out temperature during Cooling mode.No: This feature is disabledYes: Feature is active

Name: Heater low set point
Help: Heater Cut out temperature at coldest position of the spindle (thermostat knob) auto heating
ChineseHelp: Heater Cut out temperature at coldest position of the spindle (thermostat knob) auto heating

Name: Heater high set point
Help: Heater Cut out temperature at warmest position of the spindle (thermostat knob) auto heating
ChineseHelp: Heater Cut out temperature at warmest position of the spindle (thermostat knob) auto heating

Name: Heater low differential
Help: This defines the difference between the heater cut-out and the cut-in at coldest position of thermostat for auto heating
ChineseHelp: Heater Cut out temperature at coldest position of the spindle (thermostat knob) auto heating

Name: Heater High differential
Help: This defines the difference between the heater cut-out and the cut-in at warmest position of thermostat for Auto heating

Name: Energy mode delay
Help: This is the delay in minutes between the heater and the compressor operation. The heater is not allowed to start until this number of minutes has expired after the compressor has cut out and vice versa
ChineseHelp: This is the delay in minutes between the heater and the compressor operation. The heater is not allowed to start until this number of minutes has expired after the compressor has cut out and vice versa
